The paper discusses a model for metalearning that uses neural networks and deep learning techniques, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The model also deals with one-shot learning, which is a problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the benchmarks used in the paper are related to natural language processing (NLP), which falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.NE, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.CL.
